# Rule-for-Rules

When the user requests creation of Cursor rules (new rules, RULE.md, .cursor/rules, coding standards, etc.):

1. **Consult** [Cursor Docs](https://cursor.com/docs) for format, structure, and best practices
2. Use `.mdc` format in `.cursor/rules/` with YAML frontmatter
3. Configure `globs` for file-specific rules, `alwaysApply: true` for universal rules
4. Keep rules concise (under 50 lines when practical) and actionable
